description: For sale: $310,000. The McQuade Road area, near the Scenic North Shore is calling you home to a little slice of heaven on 10 acres of privacy and only 15 minutes to Duluth!  Imagine relaxing summer days watching deer, bald eagles and even the occasional moose from your 5 Bedroom, 3 bathroom home with nearly 3000 square feet of finished living space!  You are going to fall in love with your nearly 600 square foot deck where summer BBQ's are going to be a tradition in your new home or watching wildlife on a warm summer day.   An open concept main level features a large eat-in kitchen connected to the informal dining area, updated SS appliances, cherry cabinets, and an abundance of counter space.  Enjoy the privacy of seeing no neighbors, while sipping coffee in your sunny living room.  Additional amenities on the main level including the laundry room with new LG washer and dryer, half bath conveniently located off the main entrance, and two welcoming foyers.  Walk on up to the second level where you will find a spacious master suite with walk in closet, an updated full bath with a jetted tub and tiled shower. One more bedroom with original hardwood floors completes the upper level.  Enjoy more entertaining space  in your fully finished lower level where you will find brand new Luxury vinyl plank flooring in the expansive family room.  Lower level continues to amaze with 3 nice sized bedrooms with brand new carpet, utility room,  and an updated full bathroom.  The list goes on with updates that include Geo thermal heat and AC with forced air furnace, fiber cement siding, updated 200 amp electrical panel, updated plumbing, lighting throughout, and all windows 2008 and newer. Outside you will find a 24x28 heated garage with workshop area, apple tree, lilac bush, and a large level yard.   Set up an appointment today and call 6664 McQuade Road home soon.  Matterport tour available when you contact listing agent.

description: For sale: $244,900. Welcome to 4432 Tioga St! Located in Duluth's coveted Lakeside neighborhood, this 4 bed, 1 1/2 bath has much to offer its new owner. There are 2 of the 4 bedrooms and a full bath rounding out the main level. As you walk up the stairs to the second level, you will find a hallway guiding you to the other 2 bedrooms and a room off the fourth bedroom that would make an amazing walk-in closet or den/office.  There is even a 1/2 bath in this bedroom!  The basement is set up with a rec room, laundry and plenty of storage.  As a bonus to store all of your toys, the 2+ car  garage is wired with 200 amp service and has natural gas.  The 1+ car also has gas run to it!  Let's add central air, quality construction, wonderful location, gardens and a corner lot! Be the next owner to put your finishing touches on this Lakeside gem.  Call today to set up your private showing!

description: For sale: $799,900. Magnificent 4-bed 4-bath traditional home sitting on a meticulously landscaped lot on the shores of Lake Superior! This awe-inspiring property offers a private beach, and views of the big lake from almost every room in the house. The welcoming main floor offers plenty of space for entertaining in the spacious living rm and formal dining rm featuring oak hardwood flooring, a wood-burning fireplace, built-ins and french door leading out to the 680 sq ft tropical hardwood deck and amazing back yard! There is a cozy office space and an awesome green/sun rm addition with bluestone floors, vaulted ceilings, humidity resistant walls and windows, and access to the deck. The eat-in oak kitchen offers plenty of cabinet space, stainless steel and granite countertops, tiled floors and backsplash, updated lighting and views! On the 2nd floor you'll find 4 nice sized bedrooms including a large master with a private master bath, and a huge walk-in closet with a sitting room. The immaculate walk-out basement has a rec rm, and tidy laundry rm, good storage space, a sauna, and an updated 3/4 bath with a walk-in tiled shower and heated towel rack. Outside you'll find multiple perennial gardens, 2 water gardens, a garden shed and a 2-car attached garage.  Don't miss this rare opportunity to own private shoreline on the greatest of the Great Lakes!

description: For sale: $399,900. BACK ON THE MARKET--NEW PRICE!! Have you been wanting to live in one of Duluth's premier neighborhoods, but there just hasn't been an opportunity. Well, here is your chance to buy on Valley Dr, right in the heart of Hidden Valley!  This mid-century contemporary, multi-level has been uniquely designed to accommodate all types of living. From growing families to entertaining, this property has what you are longing for---space for everyone! From you moment you enter, you will be greeted by a spacious, tiled & vaulted foyer, which will make you feel like you have just entered something quite special. To the right is a huge formal living room featuring a sitting area, electric fireplace and privacy from the other living areas of the home.  There is the first of the four bedrooms to the left of the foyer. As you descend down the stairs toward the dining room with beautiful new laminate flooring and fresh paint, there is a 1/2 bath that is perfectly placed for guests and everyday use.  On this level you will also have access to the garage, the kitchen boasting granite counters, a peninsula-style eating area, formal dining room and a relaxing rec room with a unique sunken conversational area with wood-burning fireplace. There is a wonderful screened-in sun room that runs the entire back length of the house and accessible from the newly painted rec room or dining room (awesome entertaining set up). The lower level offers a rec room, workshop and bath with Jacuzzi tub and separate shower (no toilet, but one could be added). The upper level is where you will find the other 2 guest bedrooms and full bath, along with the master that is extremely bright and offers its own bath (newly renovate) with a trendy barn-style door, tile, restored cabinets and lighting.  Let's add an attached 2 car garage, EXTREMELY private back yard, additional parking for your boat or camper, concrete driveway and superb location, which adds up to a property that you don't want to let slip away! With the recent cosmetic updates and $20K reduction from last fall, it is sure not to last long with today's current market conditions! Call today for your private showing and bring your checkbook!!!!!

description: For sale: $459,900. FIRST TIME OFFERED FOR SALE IN DECADES! Here is your opportunity to own a piece of Duluth's rich architectural history. This 3 bed, 2.5 bath located on prestigious London Rd has a story to tell from it's glorious views of Lake Superior to the most unique dining room ceiling mural that depicts Duluth's rich mining and forestry industry from a by-gone era worth preserving. The main level has a wonderful circle floor plan, allowing elegant dinner parties to the most modest of gatherings. The Lake Superior views will take your breath away no matter what level you are on. The kitchen has been updated over time and offers tiled floors, custom cabinets, breakfast nook and of course a view of the lake! The living room boasts solid oak floors, a wood-burning fireplace and access to the den. Rounding off the main floor is a heated sun room and a sunken family room with another amazing view of the lake! Upstairs you will find all 3 bedrooms-the master with a 1/2 bath, full bath and plenty of storage. The basement has another 1/2 bath, storage room access to the tandem, attached garage and utility room.  As an added bonus, there is also a 1 car detached garage, paver patio, access to the lake and close to every amenity you will need from grocery, gas schools and the North Shore! Priced over $100k below assessed value for a quick sale to settle an estate. Call today and have your checkbook ready!

For sale: $389,000. Live your dream of living in a log house in the woods!!  This 5 bedroom, 3 ½ bath house on 5 acres of land near the French river is the perfect place to get away from it all.  It is located about 2 miles straight up from the McQuade harbor on Lake Superior.
Main floor has a very large master bedroom with a walk-in closet. It has a very large tiled master bathroom featuring double jacuzzi bathtub and separate shower. Large kitchen with plenty of cabinets and large pantry, a half bath is conveniently located next to the kitchen. Impressive living room with vaulted ceilings and wood burning fireplace in the great room for those cozy nights.  
The top floor has two bedrooms, a full bathroom, an office area and a relaxing loft area that overlooks the downstairs.
 Two detached 24 X 36 garages one insulated with a work shop so you have plenty of room for your toys and your cars.
The basement has a large family room, 2 bedrooms, 2 storage rooms the laundry room and the mechanical room.  Most of the walls are tongue and groove or half log siding.   Plenty of room for all your needs.
The house has a high efficient furnace, central air, water softener and an air exchanger system. It has its own well and septic system.
This is a must-see home. Go to https://www.youtube.com/user/pweisinger1 to check out videos of the house.  I don't really want to show the house until we get the Virus under control except for serious buyers.

Contact Paul at 218-343-1291 or email pweisinger@gmail.com for appointment

description: For sale: $389,900. This fantastic 4-bedroom 3-bath Congdon split-entry style home is set on a beautiful lot in Hidden Valley! You'll love how inviting this house feels in the spacious open living room and dining room featuring a decorative fireplace and a huge picture window allowing the room to fill with warmth and light. The updated kitchen offers plenty of cherry cabinets, a breakfast bar, Cambria countertops, tiled flooring, a tiled backsplash and a sliding glass door leading to a large deck and the awesome private backyard. There are 3 good sized main floor bedrooms including a master with double closets, and a half bath. The lower level offers a sunny family room with new flooring and a wood-burning fireplace, a 4th bedroom, a laundry/utility room, and newly updated 3/4 bath with a tile and stone walk-in shower. Other features include air conditioning, an 8x12 storage shed, a partially fenced backyard, updated electrical, and a sump pump with battery backup. Close to schools, parks and Tischer Creek trails, this home is not to be missed!

description: For sale: $524,900. Stop thinking about building and buy instead!! Enjoy your life in this newer 5 Bdrm, 4 Ba quality construction home with a high 3 car attached garage.  Located just below Hawks Ridge- and near the Lester Park area of Duluth this property offers all the key features you may be looking for. The home was designed with functional-carefree living in mind. From the tasteful hardy LP Smart side exterior to the interior main floor open concept living area, it was well planned out for daily living.  The main floor area has a large entry, a 1/2 Bath, spacious and bright Living room with hdwd floors + a gorgeous floor to ceiling natural stone gas fireplace, a large cook's kitchen with granite counter tops, and stainless appliances, dining area with patio doors to the back, and a mudroom with built ins.  Upstairs you will find 2 Bedrooms, a private Master Suite with walk-in closet + tiled Bath with soaker tub and walk in shower, Laundry and a full Bath.  The LL has a Family room, 2 additional Bedrooms and another full Bath. There is central air, zoned hot water heat, and air exchange!

description: For sale: $730,000. Dream house overlooking the magnificent shores of Lake Superior. A  pebble beach awaits you directly in front of your house as you walk across scenic 61 to the water.  Perfect for swimming, agate hunting, launching kayaks, paddle boards or just watching the sunrise with the soothing sounds of waves crashing. This modern home features 5 bedrooms on the same floor, 3 full baths and one 1/2 bath. As you enter you walk over a Lake Superior concrete inlay in your newly renovated dry stacked stone and concrete outdoor entry way. The modern wrap around stairs and entry greet you and opens up to the spacious floor plan.  Main floor features 1/2 bath, renovated kitchen with new tile, backsplash, Maytag stainless steel appliances gas range , paint, breakfast nook, formal dining room, and 2 living areas overlooking Lake Superior with immaculate maple hardwood floors. The larger living area is perfect for entertaining guests as you can walk thru your sliding glass doors out to the recently renovated deck with modern deck tiles, cable  railing with tigerwood , and hot tub.  You can soak in the hot tub as you hear the waves crashing on the shore. A new pellet stove was installed to keep you warm in the winter and a Haiku ceiling fan to cool in the summer.  As you go upstairs you will find 5 bedrooms, 3 full baths, and laundry area.  A recent addition converted this home from a 3 bedroom 2.5 bathroom home to a 5 bedroom 3.5 bathroom home.   The modern addition includes wood flooring throughout, 2 bedrooms with amazing Lake Superior views, new washer and dryer placed on upstairs level for convenience, storage throughout with Elfa closets, and an upgraded beautiful bathroom. From the addition a hallway leads you to the 3 other bedrooms.  The master suite offers a floor to ceiling fireplace, office nook, master bathroom, new large andersen windows and sliding glass door out to your private balcony overlooking the lake.  The large tiled basement is open floor plan with a large woodworking heated shop, furnace room, storage room, and two wonderful open spaces for additional family rooms/bedrooms. Heated and sheetrockd attached garage with spray foam insulation. This home is just .4  miles from the McQuade Safe Harbor and just 15 min. to town. Convenient location to Duluth town amenities yet far enough away to enjoy the privacy and serenity of the North shore. New Andersen windows, Nichiha fiber cement siding, clear cedar siding,  Bridger steel siding, soffit, fascia, oversized seamless gutters, garage door with smart opener, deck and balcony deck tiles, cable and tigerwood railings, 2 mini split air conditioners (one in master BR and one in addition),  boiler,  hybrid water heater, 25 year Hague water softener,  ceiling tiles in basement,  stone and concrete entry,  pellet stove, high speed fiber optic internet and invisible perimeter dog fence. Also roof new as of 2012.

description: For sale: $1,400,000. Are you ready to sit back and relax while living right on the city limits of Duluth?! 27 Eastridge Blvd is a 5-bedroom, 6-bathroom ONE OF A KIND home! Walking inside, you are welcomed by a grand staircase that leads you up to the living room. This beautiful living room is spacious in size, has a gas fireplace, and wonderful views of Lake Superior right beyond the tree line. The kitchen has granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, cabinet storage space, and a breakfast bar! The dining room is large enough to host family gatherings and has beautiful built-ins. On the other side of this spacious main level, you are given an impressively large family room. This room is used as a media/movie room. There is a game room where you have the option to play pool, darts, board games, and more! An office and a full bathroom are also on the main level. Going up to the master bedroom, you fall in love what you have! You walk into the bedroom which is so spacious and bright! A fabulous walk-in master closet and a spacious master bathroom suite that has a hydrotherapy bathtub, double vanity sinks, and a large tiled shower. You can also go outside on your private balcony to enjoy those sunrises, sunsets, and look out to the privacy that surrounds you. Attached to your master bedroom is an office! This room can be used in many ways besides an office due to its size. There is an additional storage room off the office for extra storage needs. Going to the lower level, you have 4 bedrooms, 4 bathrooms, a very generous laundry room, storage space, a den/office, and a very sizeable workout room! This workout room can hold a great amount of gym equipment. A ¾ bathroom is attached to this workout room and in that bathroom, you are given a sauna! There is also an enclosed porch off the workout room you can access from inside and deck! If you are needing more room for your workout, you can go into the at-home GYM! This gym gives you the options to play basketball, volleyball, hockey, tennis, pickle ball, 4-square, and more! The attached garage is heated, has storage rooms, additional storage above, and can fit 5-6 cars if needed! Bringing yourself outside, you see what this 5+ acres have to offer! Both the front yard and the backyard have space for so many yard games and more. The back of this home has a beautiful 3-level deck! There is even a level that holds the hot tub! There is so much to this beautiful home you won't want to miss out on! Welcome home!

description:
Recently sold: $370,000. For Sale by Zenith City Design - an extraordinary renovation of a historic 1888 Dutch Colonial!

Newly remodeled from top to bottom with an addition of a 500 sq. ft master suite with views of Lake Superior and Hawk Ridge.  This home has been completely restored and is a brand new historic home.  The perfect and sought after location in Duluth's premier lakeside neighborhood.  One block from the lakewalk, grocery store, Lester Park Elementary School, Lester Park, and Brighton Beach.  Large corner lot with beautiful established trees. 

This home has been renovated into the 21st Century with the open concept floor plan for today's living.  3 bedroom, 2 1/2 bath home.  Main level Hickory hardood floors. State of the art updates include a new furnace, new water heater with re-circulation system for instant hot water,  in-floor heating in the bathrooms, Central A/C on the first and second floor, A/C - Heat Pump in the 3rd floor master suite, hard-wired smoke and carbon monoxide detectors, all new electrical with 200 amp electrical service and arc fault gfi breakers, new plumbling throughout, all new windows, new shingle roof with metal roof on the dormer, Large corner lot, and so much more! 

Open kitchen with slide-in gas range, undercabinet microwave/convection oven, farmhouse sink, floor to ceiling maple shaker cabinets with large pantry.  

Main floor laundry, sunroom with half - bath and exquisite grand staircase.  All  bedrooms feature Mohawk 20 year carpet, and large walk-in closets. 
Incredible home - move in ready to enjoy and start your family memories.

description: Recently sold: $522,000. Looking for that fantastic view of Lake Superior with that house that is move in ready.  THIS IS IT! A very private setting only minutes to Duluth.  If you love the outdoors there are mowed trails, a seasonal creek with a beautiful rock bed, a pond and garden spaces on this 5 acre parcel.  Numerous flower beds and a vegetable garden already started.  Fruit trees, raspberries, and strawberries.  Beautiful natural wooded buffer to the north and south offer tons of privacy in your own back yard.  Greenhouse and garden shed accent this property.  A two story three car garage/barn has a  workshop and storage space!  In addition to these assets there is an RV/carport canopy.    House is move in ready with 2 large bedrooms on the main floor.  Beautiful hardwood floors on the main floor with a stone surround for the wood burning fireplace in the living room.   A large working kitchen offers plenty of counter space and storage, with a specific granite bread surface for the baker in the family.   Basement is a walkout with a wood burning fireplace insert in the family room, also a  bedroom and 3/4 bathroom!  Great Lake Superior Views from kitchen, living room and dining room!  Enjoy a glass of wine on the front deck or in the attached breezeway/sun room between the house and garage.  Perfect places to relax!!  The attached garage has a nice over sized feel and a heated separate workshop in the back!  Added Bonus:1 mile to the McQuade safe harbor/boat launch!

Other features include a new roof on the house and garage - 2016, a newly repaved driveway - 2019, a high efficient propane furnace - 2011, a Culligan water filtration system, all new carpet - 2014, new sheet rock and paint throughout, tons of closet space, custom built bookshelf in living room central air, a 30 x 48 pole bldg on a concrete slab, a dog kennel off of the garage, gardens, and so much more. Great location, just a short walk to the trails of Lester Park.

description: Recently sold: $300,000. A wonderful combination of old world charm and modern updates and conveniences, this 2+ story traditional features lots of original elements on the main level. The foyer entry features a small fireplace (decorative) and leads you to the living room with tall ceilings and a wood-burning fire place. Formal dining offers plenty of space for larger gatherings. There's a fabulous gourmet kitchen with lots of granite counter space, 5 burner gas cook top and double oven. French doors lead to the fenced back yard with its deck/patio space and garden. A 3/4 bath completes the main level. The 2nd level includes 3 bedrooms  plus an updated full bath with vintage look fixtures and a claw foot tub. The 3rd level was converted to an incredible master bedroom with a partial lake view and a professionally designed bath with shower and soaking tub. Outside, the exterior has been freshly painted and a 1-1/2 stall garage and parking pad provide extra off-street parking.

description: Recently sold: $260,000. Move right into this 3+ bedroom 2 full bath 2 car Lester Park ranch backing up to the park!  Don't be fooled on a drive by, with over 1800 finished sq. feet this home lives much larger than it appears!  A meticulously maintained home that features 3 main floor bedrooms, eat-in kitchen, and living room with beautiful oak hardwood floors upstairs.  Downstairs has a generous rec room, an "in-law" suite (non-conforming bedroom (lacks egress) and full bath, laundry and lots of storage!  Almost forgot to mention this home also has central air conditioning for those seemingly increasing number of hot days we're having in the northland.   Outside relax on your 10 x 17 deck overlooking the large, private, and fenced back yard and just outside the back fence gate, walk the short trail down to the creek!  A detached 26 x 24 two car garage gives you plenty of room for parking and storage.    Let's talk location...  This home is just steps to the extensive Lester Park Hiking trails, Lester-Amity mountain biking trails and Duluth Traverse maintained by COGS, lighted cross country ski trails and ski chalet run by the Duluth XC Ski Club, Hawk Ridge, Lester and Amity river swimming, Seven Bridges Road, Lester Park Pavilion and Playground, and close, but not too close to the Duluth Cross Town and North Shore Snowmobile trails that link to all over Northern MN.  Only blocks to Brighton Beach and the gateway to the  North Shore, MN Hwy 61's Scenic Drive! description:
Recently sold: $241,000. Love the outdoors? The sound of a babbling creek while nature watching? Hiking, biking, running, or skiing? Then this is your new home. Walk out your back door and, in less than a minute, you can enjoy 10+ miles of Duluth's premier COGGS mountain biking and hiking trails. In the winter, grab your classic or skate skis either day or night and walk 100 meters to the lit and groomed Lester-Amity ski trails, which offer 15K of varied terrain for beginner to experienced skiers through pine, aspen, and birch forests. Or, take a quick hike with the family to enjoy the waterfalls of Lester River and the natural beauty of Amity Creek.

Built in 1958, this bungalow style home rests in a quiet, safe neighborhood and is perfect for the new family or those looking to be closer to nature. This home has been well cared for, has never had any pets or smokers, and was updated with double pane windows, vinyl siding, a reshingled roof seven years ago, a partially updated kitchen, a new deck and patio door installed just last year, and an optional 6'x8' cedar barrel sauna.

description: Recently sold: $310,000. No stairs to climb here with this one level impeccably designed 3 bed, 2 bath Bruckelmyer build!  Vaulted ceilings in the living room with large windows brings in loads of natural light, enough to brighten any day.  A river rock wall with fireplace adds even more warmth to this room.  Soft grey luxury vinyl floors throughout the main level make cleaning a breeze with a modern, sleek touch and they are even heated! Loads of storage in the kitchen accentuated by beautiful custom cabinetry, with stainless steel appliances, a coffee bay, and a large working counter that passes through to the dining room.  This kitchen layout is truly a working kitchen, designed to feel open to small or large gatherings.  Just like the rest of this home, the master bedroom brings in the light with thoughtfully placed windows and a  master bath attached. The remaining bedrooms are just down the hall and have their own full bath. The amenities are endless with this home, lifetime warrantied windows, ductless mini split air conditioning, ICF walls, LP Smart Side, a compliant septic, custom solid 3 panel mission doors, and an attached garage which makes winters super easy.  Not only do you get an incredibly purposely custom designed home, there's also an expansive detached workshop with double doors, and even room for storage above. All this on five acres in Duluth Township! Close to the city, yet perfectly placed for that quiet, in-the-woods living!

description: Recently sold: $179,900. In Lester Park and just across from Grosvenor Square (green space) sits this charming & cozy 1.7 story, 2 Bdrm home.  Step up onto the covered front porch and come on in! The main level is very welcoming and consists of a  spacious living room, kitchen with eat-in area, and a large living room with alcove space for another table.  The Living room has recessed lighting, new hardwood floors, and oak woodwork. The kitchen features oak cabinetry, nice flooring and an eat-in area.  The second level has 2 Bdrms and a  full bathroom with tiled floor with oak vanity.  The basement is home to laundry area and also a great little room that could be an office or storage.  Off the back there is a nice rear deck, many raised garden beds, a firepit and a 24x26 detached 2 car garage that was built in 2002.  Fenced yard & Roof age is appx 10.  A quick walk to Lester River, or down to Super One for groceries!

description: Recently sold: $379,000. This Beautiful Home is located in the heart of the Congdon Area on a quiet street near the Hidden Valley area. Just a one minute walk from the scenic beauty of Congdon Park / Tischer Creek with its numerous waterfalls and biking and hiking trails. 2 Blocks from Ordean - East Middle School. 4 Blocks from Congdon Park Elementary or Holy Rosary School and walking distance to East High School and local stores and restaurants. The back yard is spectacular and has the feel of living in the country with the convenience of an urban location. There is also a beautiful partially heated 18' x 12' building in the back yard which has a sauna, and is currently being used as a pottery studio. This building could be used for many purposes including a Man Cave, She Shed, Play House, or just additional heated storage. Some of this homes many features include a Security System, 2 Split A/C units which cool all of the bedrooms and most of the home, 2 Newly remodeled Bathrooms, New Epoxy Painted Garage Floor, New Garage Door, Air Exchangers, Hardwood Floors, 6 Panel Birch Doors Chromatherapy Air Jetted Tub with heated Backrest and LED lighting, a Large Deck, an underground lawn irrigation system, 2 fireplaces, and much more. The Large Family room could also be divided into a 4th bedroom and still have plenty of room for a study or den with a fireplace.

description: Recently sold: $194,000. Wonderful move-in ready Lester Park bungalow with gleaming hardwood floors, remodeled kitchen with newer cabinets, granite tile countertops, stainless appliances, and beautiful low maintenance slate flooring. The main floor features an open kitchen dining area with breakfast nook over looking the park-like back yard and is perfect for entertaining.  The living room features an efficient Jotul wood burning fireplace and hardwood floors. The main floor also includes a nice sized bedroom with hardwood floors and full bath.  Upstairs you'll find a 2nd bedroom with an updated bath en suite including a relaxing jacuzzi tub.  The lower level features a large rec room/media room, 3/4 bath with sauna, laundry and storage areas.  Part of the rec room has potential for 3rd bedroom with a door and egress window. Outside you'll find a cozy deck overlooking a private backyard with firepit and 2 stall 24 x 24 detached garage. There is a platted but unbuilt street to the east giving you a little extra elbow room with this home and wildlife sightings are common! This home also has an newer gas furnace, central air, newer roof, redone lateral line, low maintenance metal siding, updated kitchen and baths!  Just move right in and enjoy this home located a half mile to Lester Park with river swimming, fishing, hiking, skiing, and nationally renowned mountain biking trails, Hawk Ridge Nature Preserve, Hawk Ridge Bird Observatory, and the Duluth Traverse Trail.  It's also only a 1/2 mile to the grocery store or gas station, 4 blocks from Lester Park Elementary and less than a mile to Brighton beach and the scenic north shore of Lake Superior. See it today!

description: Recently sold: $435,000. This spectacular home still has that" brand new" home feel to it! Located on a cul-de sac in Hawk Ridge Estates you will find this 3++ bedroom 3 bath home with great amenities. Great front porch welcomes you to step inside to the main level with office/den, powder bath,laundry room and fabulous garage entry w/ closet and space for cubbies. Eat in Kitchen has breakfast bar, quartz countertops, stainless appliances and pantry w/ pullouts. There is a new maintenance free deck off dining area.  This area is open to living room w/ gas fireplace.  Front entry, den, kitchen, dining,powder bath and living all have gleaming hardwood flooring. Upstairs you will find master suite with walk in closet,and a full bath w/ tiled floor and shower.  2 more bedrooms and another full bath and a BONUS/FAMILY room that has ample space.   The lower level has 9 ft ceilings, large windows and is LOADED with potential! Home has central air, 2 laundry chutes on upper level, insulated garage, 3 panel doors and trails in backyard which lead to the Amity Creek Trails and the Lester Park Multi Use Trail Center (COGGS).  This is an amazing home that won't last long!!

description:
Recently sold: $175,000. Quiet 5+ acre two story  home minutes from downtown Duluth!  Whether you are looking for a weekend getaway up the North Shore or work in the city but want to be just far enough away from the crowds, this beautiful home offers it all!  2+ bedroom, in floor heat on main floor, baseboard heat upstairs,  storage shed,located on a dirt road just 6 miles from East Duluth.  This is an outdoorsman's  dream with Mcquade Safe Harbor walking distance from your front walk out deck.  Located on a wooded 5+ acre lot with abundant wildlife.  Just outside city limits, rifle and bow hunting out your backdoor.  Newer stackable washer and dryer (2009) and all appliances included.  New laminate wood floors 2015 throughout main floor, new carpet on stairs and upstairs living room 2015, and hardwood tile in master bedroom.  In floor heat (two zones), walk out patio door to deck, back door entrance, large bathroom, breakfast bar, dishwasher, electric stove, main floor bedroom patio doors out back, outdoor fire pit, drilled well and city sewer. Propane heat.  Space to build a two stall garage.  This is a great piece of land just outside of Duluth! 10 miles to downtown Duluth, 15 miles to Two Harbors.  Enjoy the Clearwater Grille within a mile from your house and a gas station less than a mile.  

Couch & Love Seat, Window AC unit, and outside dog kennel included in sale

description: Recently sold: $215,000. Located along the Lester River with the Lakewalk, hiking, biking, and skiing trails right out the door, this beautiful 2 bedroom condo is living easy. description: Recently sold: $143,000. Lakeside is home to this solid, well-cared for bungalow. This perfect starter home features 2 bedrooms on the main level, hardwood floors and new carpet, a completely remodeled bathroom including new plumbing and electrical, a super functional kitchen, a large living/dining area, tons of natural light, and a den/office with a bar in the lower level. The one car garage has extra storage in the handy lean-to, there's off-street parking with the asphalt driveway, the roof is fairly new and the vinyl siding is maintenance free, and there's a nice back yard to play in. Enjoy the excellent location close to schools, Lester Park Trails, and only blocks from the Lakewalk and Lake Superior.

description: Recently sold: $198,500. 5215 Tioga St is a 3 bed, 1 3/4 bath home with a 2 car garage in Lakeside! This home has beautiful natural woodwork and hardwood floors throughout. description: Recently sold: $229,000. 4021 Pitt St is a spacious and lovely 3 bed, 1 3/4 bath home with a 1 car tuck under garage in Lakeside! This split-level home has hardwood floors, two fireplaces (one gas and one wood-burning), built in storage, a nice sized family room, open kitchen and dining area, and much more. All three bedrooms are upstairs along with a full bathroom (with a skylight and heated floors!). In the basement is a big family room with gas fireplace, an office area with built in shelves and cabinets, a 3/4 bathroom, and a laundry room just off of the side entrance. The main level has the kitchen, dining room and a spacious living room with a wood burning fireplace and big windows to bring in lots of natural light. Off of the living room is a 3 season screen porch, which leads to an open deck with built in benches. Nice big back yard with a fire pit area, storage shed, and mature trees for shade. Beautiful perennials and landscaping in the yard as well. Located close to schools, parks, a golf course, and Lakeside shopping and restaurants, this is a gem of a home!

description: Recently sold: $430,000. Is your dream an elegant home, in a private, serene setting in the woods? Your search is over! Welcome to 1818 Shilhon Road, a  stunning home nestled on 20 acres, just minutes up the shore. The wow factor is instant as you enter this charming home! A living room, with vaulted ceilings, a Franklin stove, and stunning walls of windows, you will be impressed. The dining area overlooks the sculpted backyard, and through beautiful windows, you will revel in watching all the woodland animals as you dine. The kitchen was designed with the chef in mind! Plenty of counter space, beautiful cabinets, and a grand center island.  As you step through the french doors onto the sprawling deck, imagine all the time you will spend here. The first, of five bedrooms, is situated on this main level, and a 3/4 bath is steps away, making it perfect for guests.  The staircase leads you up to the second floor that hosts an open office space, and two bedrooms.  The master overlooks  the front grounds, has a lovely full walk thru bath and a walk-in closet. The lower level hosts a family room, game area, two more huge bedrooms, and a 3/4 bath. The sellers are installing a brand new boiling system! The "shack," hosts a hot tub room, snack room w/ fridge, bar, and cabinets.There is an impressive workshop with storage galore! You will love the pole barn! Enjoy hours of outdoor activities from walking trails, hunting, 4-wheeling, snowmobiles, etc. Electric: $4800yr Propane: $500.00yr

Recently sold: $425,090. Home is nestled in upper Congdon 7 bedrooms, 5 bathrooms, 2 car garage open layout kitchen dining room. Large rec room on the lower level with bathroom, laundry and storage. Upper level bedrooms, bath, lounge area and master en suite. Large backyard with nice size deck for entertaining. East school district. Call to set up a showing! Brokered And Advertised By: Tellor Realty, LLC Listing Agent: Tracey Tellor

description: Recently sold: $465,000. Spectacular Hidden Valley home on a quiet dead end street, within walking distance to Northland Country Club's 10th hole. This home features 4 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, an attached oversized 2 car garage and a walkout basement. The front foyer invites you to spacious living room with bay windows, hardwood floors, gas fireplace and built-in cabinets. So many updates! The open floor plan includes a living room, kitchen and dining area with sliding doors to new deck (2017) and stair access to the beautifully landscaped backyard (2016). Kitchen recently updated (2014) with quartz countertops, subway tile backsplash and newer appliances. Kitchen also boasts a large peninsula and breakfast bar that easily seats four. Three bedrooms are located on the main floor, including a full bath and a master suite with walk-in closet and 3/4 bath. The lower level features a large fourth bedroom, 3/4 bath, sunny laundry room and a spacious family room with another gas fireplace and sliding doors to the patio and beautiful fenced-in backyard. description: Recently sold: $234,900. This home has been carefully updated throughout so all you have to do is move your things in and enjoy the views of Lake Superior. The kitchen features quartz countertops from a local company, and the original built in cupboards stand out on the main wall among the farmhouse sink with a garbage disposal. There are three bedrooms upstairs, and one has a large bonus room that can be used as a bedroom, nursery, or office. The master bedroom has views of the lake, a big closet as well as a walk in closet that is currently being used as a nursery. The upstairs bathroom is updated to match the downstairs bathroom design and is a full bath. A top of the line natural gas furnace was is installed in 2016 and there is an almost-fully fenced backyard to keep kids and pets away from the street. The basement has been cleaned, waterproofed, and painted and many new windows have been installed.

description: Recently sold: $354,000. Spotless and well-maintained ranch-style home set on 10 gorgeous acres!  This one-owner home was built in 1992 with an open floor plan.  Main floor features an open living and kitchen area.  Kitchen has beautiful gleaming maple wood floor, subway tiles and patio doors leading to deck which overlooks beautiful gardens.  Living room has a Lopi gas fireplace and new Marvin windows which allow for lots of natural sunlight.  Master bedroom has full bath and double closets.  Two more bedrooms and another full bath complete the main level.  Downstairs is a new ¾'s bath, a family room,  a den (4th bedroom possible but egress window may not make current code standards) and an unfinished area that would make a great game room or more bedrooms. description: Recently sold: $165,000. There is also a nice deck and rustic unique garden shed out back. The roofs on the house and garage were replaced in 2008 and the exterior is maintenance free vinyl. Detached large 2-car garage fully insulated, built in 1983, and includes a professionally designed 12x24 office space, the garage access is off Crosley St and gives you easy access for parking and storing all your toys and enough room to park an RV. There is also off street parking for 1 car in the front of the house, and 2-4 cars in back. Garage Studio could be removed for more parking inside if needed.

Full listing planned for Labor Day!

Recently sold: $323,000. Tucked back on a dead end road on 5 acres of land lies this beautiful 4 bedroom 3 bath home with large open floor plan. This home features 9ft white pine ceilings with maple crown molding, Marvin windows providing a lot of natural light and in-floor radiant heating through out. Walk into a welcoming entryway with storage closets that flow into a living room, dining room and kitchen featuring bamboo laminate flooring. The living room has a gas fireplace to keep cozy, a dining room with a walk out deck and a gorgeous kitchen with stone back splash, cherry cabinets, stainless steel appliances, 2 ovens and a large pantry. The main floor also includes laundry, guest bedroom and bath, master bedroom and bath with walk in closet and beautifully tiled stone shower with jet tub. The upstairs includes plenty of storage, office/den space, 2 bedrooms and 1 bathroom. All of this and only 5 minutes from town. This home is the best of city and rural living. Don't miss your chance!

Recently sold: $90,000. Come experience the charm and character of this 3 Bedroom Lakeside Traditional! Big, gorgeous wood-trimmed windows light up the living room, while the wood-burning fireplace keeps it cozy. A large entry, formal dining room, and kitchen complete the main level. Upstairs are three bedrooms and the full bath. Basement includes a workshop space. Large corner lot is partially fenced and landscaped with hedges.
